56
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:09,360
But he was the lead in Busjack 2.

57
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:12,260
It's becuase I saw that.

58
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:16,180
I doesn't stink that much!

59
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:20,180
OK, let's go! This is our heroine! She's awesome!

60
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:22,940
Boom! Taira Yuna-chan!

61
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:25,380
A super popular actress!

62
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:29,620
The main character, Hamasaki Iku, is Taira Yuna!

63
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:32,300
Just the last year, she appeared in 9 movies!

64
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:37,560
Playing the heroine in many heart-warming love-romances. A popular young actress!

65
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,320
So shall we get started?

66
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,500
Start what?
- "What?", we're gonna watch it.

67
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,140
The finished product?
- The finished product.

68
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:46,080
You're not finishing it.

69
00:03:47,140 --> 00:03:48,820
It is finished.

70
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:53,980
I did read your script one time. I don't think it's as rich as that though.

71
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,720
You praised me, didn't you?

72
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:56,860
What are you talking about?

73
00:03:56,860 --> 00:03:59,380
After you read it, when we were in the restroom...

74
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:03,020
You said, "You're a smart fool."
- "A smart fool."?

75
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:07,360
I didn't say it like that. No, I...

76
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:10,640
read your script and thought it was a little amusing.

77
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:15,120
Now, how it plays out, I'll have to see it to understand.

78
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:19,080
This is Tsukitei Housei's first directorial project.

79
00:04:19,080 --> 00:04:19,680
VTR...

80
00:04:20,380 --> 00:04:20,880
enjoy.

81
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:22,220
what?

82
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:30,520
Written and Directed by Tsukitei Housei
Let's Go Home Together

83
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,840
Please...be my girlfriend!

84
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,240
I'm sorry.

85
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:51,520
C'mon, Iku! How many is that now?

86
00:04:51,820 --> 00:04:55,080
I told you he was a good catch!

87
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:56,120
Is he?

88
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:59,640
Graduating alone is lonely too, y'know.

89
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:03,800
Or...is there another boy you like!?

90
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,100
That's not it!

91
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,140
what~

92
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,280
you can tell me.

93
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:10,980
huh?

94
00:05:13,340 --> 00:05:15,660
[Art Room]

95
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:27,880
(♪ Himawari no Yakusoku - Hata Motohiro)

96
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:46,300
Teacher!

97
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:48,960
Iku...

98
00:05:49,460 --> 00:05:50,740
Are you going home?

99
00:05:53,380 --> 00:05:54,580
Let's go home together!

100
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:04,280
To find out you're a pizza-bun fan, too.

101
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:05,240
We're the same.

102
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:09,420
Also, aren't you a fan of Hata Motohiro?

103
00:06:09,420 --> 00:06:10,940
I'm a fan, too.

104
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:12,960
We even have pendants.

105
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:14,540
We're so much alike.

106
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:17,080
It's just coincidence.

107
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:21,280
More importantly, you better get home soon, Iku.

108
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:26,080
Right. That name, Iku. I don't care for it.

109
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:30,240
Iku as in "to live". Sounds kinda lame.

110
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:37,320
Isn't that the name your dying mother gave you so you could live on?

111
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,320
Don't talk like that.

112
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:43,840
How do you know that story, Teacher?

113
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:49,360
I...I heard it from someone.

114
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,380
Right. Just by chance.

115
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:05,580
Tanaka-sensei! We have a problem!

116
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:11,440
[Principal's Office]

117
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:14,040
What's your teacher teaching!?

118
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:18,540
I keep hearing he's walking with my daughter!

119
00:07:18,540 --> 00:07:19,580
It's not like that!

120
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:22,920
Sir, please calm down. It must be some kind of misunderstanding.

121
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:24,520
It ain't no misunderstanding!

122
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:26,900
Get it together! I'm really pissed!

123
00:07:26,900 --> 00:07:27,520
Excuse me!

124
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:32,400
Why you! You're a teacher and you're nearing my daughter!

125
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:36,820
You bastard! Don't you come near my daughter!

126
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:38,520
I...I understand.

127
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,400
I won't...near her again.

128
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:43,280
Excuse me.

129
00:07:49,140 --> 00:07:49,640
Oy!

130
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,520
You gonna run away again?

131
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:09,920
[Graduation Ceremony]

132
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,300
Teacher?

133
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,120
This is where you were.

134
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:35,780
Found you.

135
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,280
Iku...

136
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:41,360
Congratulations on graduating.

137
00:08:42,160 --> 00:08:43,220
Thank you.

138
00:08:47,820 --> 00:08:49,980
Today I graduate from school, but...

139
00:08:52,860 --> 00:08:54,860
I can't graduate from you.

140
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:02,240
Tanaka-sensei...

141
00:09:03,660 --> 00:09:04,440
I love you.

142
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:11,400
Iku.

143
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:15,240
I love you too.

144
00:09:18,680 --> 00:09:19,400
Really?

145
00:09:21,620 --> 00:09:23,340
Do you know why I love you?

146
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:26,600
It's because...

147
00:09:29,980 --> 00:09:32,100
I'm your real father.

148
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:46,520
A joke, so you don't have to date me.

149
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,240
It's not a joke.

150
00:09:59,040 --> 00:09:59,800
Is that...

151
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:01,400
me?

152
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:03,920
No...

153
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:10,680
Your mother, Misako, and I...

154
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:14,880
along with your dad, Masato, were all friends in college.

155
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:20,480
We were college classmates.

156
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:24,280
Me, the gloomy guy, only interested in art.

157
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:26,700
From Osaka, the always funny, Masa.

158
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,320
And the sickly, but always happy, Misako.

159
00:10:30,020 --> 00:10:32,920
We were from different backgrounds, but were always together.

160
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:38,120
I started dating your mother a year later.

161
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,760
It was a great time.

162
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,840
I was so happy.

163
00:10:42,900 --> 00:10:43,900
And still...

164
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:47,100
You're so selfish!

165
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:50,000
Think about Misako!

166
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:56,240
I couldn't give up my dream of being an artist and left for France.

167
00:10:57,560 --> 00:11:01,760
I had no idea you were inside your mother's stomach.

168
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,080
Misako...

169
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:08,400
didn't want to get in the way of my dream.

170
00:11:09,420 --> 00:11:10,240
Supporting...

171
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:14,600
her decision to raise you on her own...

172
00:11:15,020 --> 00:11:16,160
was Masa.

173
00:11:17,740 --> 00:11:18,960
When you were born...

174
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:20,680
and after Misako passed away...

175
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:23,640
Masa raised you on his own.

176
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:29,600
Now you understand, Iku.

177
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,860
I'm your real father.

178
00:11:34,980 --> 00:11:35,980
That's why I can't...

179
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,120
Stop.

180
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,940
I understand now.

181
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:42,560
But...

182
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,400
you're not my dad.

183
00:11:49,060 --> 00:11:50,060
My dad...

184
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:54,000
my real dad...

185
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:58,000
there's only one in the world.

186
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:13,820
♪ Why...do...

187
00:12:14,460 --> 00:12:16,560
♪ you...cry?

188
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:23,060
♪ When I haven't even cried yet.

189
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:25,840
♪ You...grieve...

190
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,820
♪ more than me...

191
00:12:27,820 --> 00:12:28,800
Teacher?

192
00:12:29,980 --> 00:12:30,760
Thank you.

193
00:12:31,940 --> 00:12:33,760
For telling me the truth.

194
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:39,280
The name, Iku.

195
00:12:39,520 --> 00:12:40,840
I love, now!

196
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:54,760
Let's go home together!

197
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:58,900
♪ Wanna be by your side...

198
00:12:58,900 --> 00:13:03,160
♪ to do anything for you...

199
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:08,280
♪ if it's within my power~

200
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:11,260
♪ Always for you~

201
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:14,280
♪ Forever for you~

202
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:18,180
♪ I wish you to stay smiling.

203
00:13:18,180 --> 00:13:19,200
Her smile...

204
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:23,320
looks more and more like yours.

205
00:13:23,820 --> 00:13:27,600
♪ her unbending gentleness...

206
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:32,440
♪ her warmth, her everything~

207
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:35,820
♪ From now on, I too...

208
00:13:35,820 --> 00:13:38,840
♪ hope to achieve...

209
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:43,000
♪ that happiness, in my heart...

210
00:13:43,220 --> 00:13:47,740
♪ I now realize~

211
00:13:52,260 --> 00:13:53,380
What the hell!

212
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:56,160
What's wrong?

213
00:13:56,260 --> 00:13:57,980
What kind of tears are those?

214
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:00,720
It's bad.

215
00:14:01,460 --> 00:14:02,480
What's bad?

216
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:04,160
Well it is bad.

217
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:05,440
It could go either way.

218
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,440
No.

219
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:07,460
Wait.

220
00:14:08,020 --> 00:14:08,520
Um...

221
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,840
I'm crying so much I can't breathe.

222
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:14,500
Wow...really...

223
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:15,280
you're...

224
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,760
you're serious, aren't you?

225
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,920
I heard a rumor...

226
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:22,160
you cried when writing the script.

227
00:14:22,580 --> 00:14:23,540
Is that so?

228
00:14:23,560 --> 00:14:24,440
You cried.

229
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:26,360
Seriously?
- I cried as I wrote it.

230
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:31,020
What part was the sad part?

231
00:14:33,460 --> 00:14:35,020
What part was the sad part?

232
00:14:35,020 --> 00:14:35,640
That's...

233
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:38,220
um, Iku...

234
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:42,060
the person she liked all this time, was her real father.

235
00:14:42,060 --> 00:14:45,860
But she doesn't accept him as her real father.

236
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:46,560
Right?

237
00:14:48,620 --> 00:14:49,540
he raised her...

238
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,240
Sorry, but...

239
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:57,220
you're copying, "Yamachan ain't quitting".

240
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:00,100
With this setting.

241
00:15:02,140 --> 00:15:04,400
We can't take you seriously.

242
00:15:04,860 --> 00:15:06,100
But you're serious, aren't you?

243
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:07,320
It was amazing.

244
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,520
Isn't the timeline a little off?

245
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:11,260
She suddenly graduates.

246
00:15:11,260 --> 00:15:13,520
That's because graduation was nearing.

247
00:15:13,780 --> 00:15:15,380
We didn't know that!

248
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:19,880
You would know. It's because you weren't watching properly!

249
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:22,280
Talking and jibber-jabbering.

250
00:15:22,280 --> 00:15:24,680
It didn't even feel like Spring.

251
00:15:25,140 --> 00:15:27,060
You couldn't tell what season it was.

252
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,980
No, it all flows...smoothly.

253
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:34,640
Yes, all the supporting scenes were taken.

254
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:37,760
What does Tanaka think? You worked the hardest!

255
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:44,900
No, no, no. Actually, there wasn't much direction.

256
00:15:44,980 --> 00:15:45,480
Yeah!

257
00:15:46,140 --> 00:15:47,660
A behind the scenes glimpse!

258
00:15:47,660 --> 00:15:50,520
Director Housei and his problem scenes.

259
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,640
You're learning your lines now?

260
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:55,920
Sorry, sorry. I can't remember them.

261
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:59,920
Do we need that part with you singing?

262
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,300
Of course we do.

263
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:03,220
What would we do without it?

264
00:16:04,620 --> 00:16:05,500
What is this?

265
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:07,500
What the!

266
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:09,940
Who are you?

267
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:14,400
Does a director appear this much?

268
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:18,600
It would've been fine with just the music.

269
00:16:19,560 --> 00:16:21,860
Yea, no, what do you think Matsumoto-san?

270
00:16:22,260 --> 00:16:24,000
What do you think about the song?

271
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:28,880
Well, it's a lil out of place. It's kinda like you were from another dimension.
- Yes, yes...

272
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:31,120
Like no one can really see you.
- Yes, yes...

273
00:16:31,820 --> 00:16:33,620
You keep saying, "Yes, yes" but...

274
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:36,260
You didn't even explain any of that!

275
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:39,420
Ah! Is that what you meant?
- Yes, yes...

276
00:16:39,420 --> 00:16:42,400
My only scene...

277
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,740
it's so small to begin with.

278
00:16:44,740 --> 00:16:49,000
To have my small lines cut out was quite the shock.

279
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:57,460
I keep hearing he's walking with my daughter!

280
00:16:57,460 --> 00:16:58,520
It's not like that.

281
00:16:58,520 --> 00:17:01,780
Sir, please calm down. It must be some kind of misunderstanding.

282
00:17:01,780 --> 00:17:03,420
It ain't no misunderstanding!

283
00:17:03,420 --> 00:17:05,740
Get it together! I'm really pissed!

284
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:06,240
Excuse me!

285
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:10,100
He wanted to retake it.

286
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:13,600
I didn't think it was a real take!

287
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:18,260
I thought it was a practice run. "OK! It's OK." EH!?

288
00:17:18,420 --> 00:17:22,500
I thought it was rehearsal so I wasn't satisfied.

289
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:23,660
No, it was good.

290
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:29,660
I wanted the Principal to do it halfheartedly so it was really good.

291
00:17:29,660 --> 00:17:34,240
But my voice wasn't quite ready, kinda hoarse.

292
00:17:35,300 --> 00:17:41,240
This is the take Matsumoto wasn't satisfied with.

293
00:17:43,080 --> 00:17:44,200
Where does Hamada-san sit?

294
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:49,280
What's with this guy?

295
00:17:50,780 --> 00:17:51,440
What the...

296
00:17:51,940 --> 00:17:52,580
Please.

297
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:57,280
All cast.

298
00:17:58,580 --> 00:17:59,620
Thank you very much.

299
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:04,600
Matsumoto-san, you're over here. Thank you very much.

300
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:09,360
Here's Yuna-chan! Thank you very much!

301
00:18:10,620 --> 00:18:12,140
Director, will my feet show?

302
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:14,040
Your feet?

303
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:15,200
Would this be fine?

304
00:18:15,340 --> 00:18:17,400
Will the feet show? How's the angle?

305
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:20,960
You decide!

306
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,440
You're the Director!

307
00:18:23,260 --> 00:18:25,120
Should I wear shoes?

308
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:28,820
Shoes? You're fine if they don't show. How's the angle?

309
00:18:28,820 --> 00:18:31,640
Shouldn't I wear them?
- Says he should wear them!

310
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:34,060
They won't show.
- The won't show!

311
00:18:36,060 --> 00:18:37,680
This part's the foreshadowing.

312
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:39,180
It's the heart of the story.

313
00:18:39,580 --> 00:18:41,060
You're learning your lines now?

314
00:18:41,060 --> 00:18:44,140
Sorry, sorry. I can't remember them.

315
00:18:44,140 --> 00:18:45,620
Not, "I can't remember them."!

316
00:18:45,620 --> 00:18:48,300
For real, I can't remember them.
- Let's stop with the, "I can't remember"

317
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:52,140
I keep saying the same lines so I can't remember.
- How can that be?

318
00:18:55,140 --> 00:18:57,500
We have you properly in the frame so...

319
00:19:00,780 --> 00:19:01,500
What was that?

320
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:06,320
Ready...and...start!

321
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:07,200
OY!

322
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:11,180
What's your teacher teaching!?

323
00:19:11,180 --> 00:19:15,540
I keep hearing he's walking with my daughter!

324
00:19:15,540 --> 00:19:18,440
It's not like that! I was the one who...

325
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:22,700
Sir, please calm down. It must be some kind of misunderstanding.

326
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:26,020
It ain't no misunderstanding! I'm hearing it!

327
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:28,360
Yes! We got it! Thank you very much!

328
00:19:28,660 --> 00:19:29,400
(Director: OK!)

329
00:19:30,780 --> 00:19:32,120
We got an "OK" from the Director.

330
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,000
(Director: OK!)

331
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:36,760
(Director: Good! Good! Good!)

332
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,440
Was that good?

333
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:42,100
It's good.
- I didn't like it.

334
00:19:44,360 --> 00:19:46,880
It kinda got rattle-y.

335
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:52,180
I didn't think it was a real take...

336
00:19:54,380 --> 00:19:55,680
Are you kidding?

337
00:19:56,260 --> 00:19:58,420
That might be a good take.

338
00:19:59,060 --> 00:20:02,000
What does Tanaka think? You worked the hardest!

339
00:20:04,100 --> 00:20:09,140
No, no, no. There wasn't much direction.

340
00:20:09,140 --> 00:20:09,980
Yeah!

341
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:11,020
Felt neglected?

342
00:20:11,020 --> 00:20:14,940
Felt neglected so I wasn't sure what to do.

343
00:20:14,940 --> 00:20:16,140
He wouldn't tell us anything.

344
00:20:16,140 --> 00:20:19,960
I wasn't exactly sure how to deliver my lines...

345
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:22,780
No, in fact, I was pondering that too.

346
00:20:23,780 --> 00:20:24,420
Pondering?

347
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:26,020
Were you pondering?

348
00:20:26,540 --> 00:20:33,380
[Director Housei's pondering scene.]

349
00:20:33,380 --> 00:20:34,840
OK. We got it.

350
00:20:34,840 --> 00:20:36,020
Oh, oh, nice, nice.

351
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:38,160
That last part...

352
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:40,160
maybe she's looking at Tanaka?

353
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:47,040
On the outside looking in...

354
00:20:47,740 --> 00:20:49,960
Director, how was Hamada's acting?

355
00:20:50,280 --> 00:20:52,120
I was...moved.

356
00:20:52,140 --> 00:20:53,500
What are you talking about?

357
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:57,280
Um...Papa to Nacchan, was it?

358
00:20:58,040 --> 00:21:00,360
I saw that back in the day and...

359
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:02,120
you've really matured.

360
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:06,400
So he wasn't good back then?

361
